  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM6.6.8">
<l>murukkilaṅku kaṉittuvarvāyp piṉṉai kēḷvaṉ maṉṉellām muṉṉaviyac ceṉṟu veṉṟic</l>
<l>cerukkaḷattut tiṟalaḻiyac ceṟṟa vēntaṉ cirantuṇintāṉ tiruvaṭinuñ ceṉṉi vaippīr</l>
<l>irukkilaṅku tirumoḻivā yeṇṭō ḷīcaṟ keḻilmāṭa meḻupatucey tulaka māṇṭa</l>
<l>tirukkulattu vaḷaccōḻaṉ cērnta kōyil tirunaṟaiyūr maṇimāṭañ cērmiṉ kaḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>You who would place your heads on the divine feet of the beloved of Piṉṉai,</l>
<l rend="indent">with red lips [like] the bright fruit of the coral [tree],</l>
<l>Of him who severed the head of the hateful king,</l>
<l rend="indent">arriving victorious on the battlefield so that [the enemy’s] strength</l>
<l rend="indent">was destroyed, once when all the warriors were exterminated,</l>
<l>Gather at the beautiful raised shrine in Tirunaṟaiyūr, the temple where came</l>
<l rend="indent">the prosperous Cōḻa of the eminent clan that rules the world,</l>
<l>Having built seventy beautiful raised shrines to eight-armed Īśa</l>
<l rend="indent">[on whose] lips are the illuminating sacred words of the Ṛg.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
